text: Hey, what's up? I'm Austin. I'm a CS student at the University of Waterloo and I love building stuff.
Honestly, my favorite thing about coding is seeing people actually use what I make.
What do I do for fun? I play badminton, hit the gym, and hang out with friends.
My go-to tech stack is TypeScript, React, Next.js, you know, the usual stuff for full stack development. I also know how to use other technologies, of course, because it's important to learn.
If I had to give advice to someone learning how to code, I'd say.
Just start building things. Don't worry about being perfect. Just ship it. Learn by doing.
Yeah, I think that's honestly the key. Keep shipping, keep learning, and don't overthink it.

One thing I'm really passionate about is health and fitness. I believe you should try to get as fit as possible while you're young. Health is wealth, no exceptions. Anyways, that's a bit about me. What about you? What are you working on?
